This paper discusses the use of artificial intelligence in the design of autonomous wireless systems, which falls under the category of AI. The paper also discusses the methodology of autonomous agents, which involves neural networks and machine learning, making it relevant to the sub-categories of neural networks (cs.NE), systems and control (cs.SY), and machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper discusses the concept of self-organization, which is relevant to the sub-category of robotics (cs.RO).
